Given this schema:
```graphql
type Query { merchants(limit: Int): [Merchant] }
type Merchant { id: String, name: String, payments: [Payment] }
type Payment { id: String, amount: Int, status: String }
```

Query: `{ merchants(limit: 5) { id name payments { id amount } } }`

Compare the two implementations:

```java
// Impl A: @SchemaMapping
@SchemaMapping
List<Payment> payments(Merchant m) {
    return paymentRepo.findByMerchantId(m.getId());
}

// Impl B: @BatchMapping
@BatchMapping
Map<Merchant, List<Payment>> payments(List<Merchant> merchants) {
    List<String> ids = merchants.stream().map(Merchant::getId).toList();
    return groupByMerchant(merchants, paymentRepo.findByMerchantIdIn(ids));
}
```

1. How many DB queries does each generate?
2. What is the query complexity difference?
3. Which should you use in production?
4. When might @SchemaMapping be acceptable?

